‐ We interrupt
this scheduled programming

26
00:02:26,355 --> 00:02:27,981
to bring you a breaking story.

27
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,608
MAN:
The police are currently engaged

28
00:02:29,608 --> 00:02:30,942
in a high‐speed chase

29
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:32,611
with what appears to be
the Headless Rider!

30
00:02:32,611 --> 00:02:33,904
‐ Not good.

31
00:02:33,904 --> 00:02:36,073
Not good. Not good.
Not good. Not good!

32
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,917
‐ [chuckles]

33
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:04,476
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

34
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:10,315
‐ Oh!

35
00:03:10,315 --> 00:03:12,192
‐ Ha! Don't think so.

36
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:14,653
Central,
this is Ikebukuro Three.

37
00:03:14,653 --> 00:03:17,072
Send backup to my location.

38
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:18,990
IZAYA:
Huh. Never would've thought

39
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,826
something like that
would happen.

40
00:03:20,826 --> 00:03:21,827
MAN: Unbelievable!

41
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:23,578
‐ So that's Kinnosuke Kuzuhara,

42
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:25,747
the motorcycle cop
I've been hearing about.

43
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:29,376
Can't tell
if this is good timing or bad.

44
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:32,712
[classical music]

45
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,798
‐ The rider in black,
at least for now,

46
00:03:34,798 --> 00:03:37,050
is remaining silent
up on that rooftop.

47
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,510
[gasps]

48
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:40,846
Look at that!

49
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:45,142
It's a huge black object!

50
00:03:45,142 --> 00:03:46,726
‐ Think you're Lupin the Third?

51
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:49,354
‐ Stay with us
as we continue our coverage

52
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:50,814
of that mysterious entity!

53
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:52,691
‐ Hmm.

54
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:54,860
‐ We'll bring you more exciting
details right after this‐‐

55
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:57,571
‐ [gasps]
It totally is mysterious!

56
00:03:57,571 --> 00:03:59,322
How'd that bike
turn into a horse?

57
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:00,949
How'd it do that? How?

58
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:02,325
I mean, it's not CGI, right?

59
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:04,411
‐ Not so loud.
‐ Oh, I'm sorry.

60
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:06,705
But this stupid news
cutting into Yuhei's special

61
00:04:06,705 --> 00:04:07,831
pisses me off.

62
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:09,791
I just can't contain myself!

63
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,543
Let's go.
I want to see.

64
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:13,128
It's all happening
right around here,

65
00:04:13,128 --> 00:04:14,671
so come on‐‐
I can't take it anymore.

66
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:15,839
I want to go see!

67
00:04:15,839 --> 00:04:17,507
‐ Calm down.
‐ I want to go see!

68
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:20,218
‐ Ah! I'm sorry!
I'm sorry, Ruri!

69
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:23,263
I'll calm down!
I'll calm down, okay?

70
00:04:24,306 --> 00:04:25,390
[coughing]

71
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:28,685
No more habanero spray, please.

72
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:30,103
Think about it.

73
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:32,564
We're so lucky
to be living in an exciting city

74
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:34,065
with all this going on.

75
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:35,609
How thrilling is that, you know?

76
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:36,860
It's super thrilling, right?

77
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:39,863
Super magical.
So super badass!

78
00:04:39,863 --> 00:04:41,198
[grunting]

79
00:04:41,198 --> 00:04:42,783
‐ It's so exciting.

80
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:48,163
[police siren wailing]

81
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:50,582
‐ A mysterious object
is circling above‐‐

82
00:04:50,582 --> 00:04:52,292
MAX: Whoa!

83
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:53,585
What's its deal?

84
00:04:53,585 --> 00:04:55,253
What the heck
am I even looking at here?

85
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,506
It's something
mind‐blowingly awesome.

86
00:04:57,506 --> 00:04:59,925
Something
out‐of‐this‐world powerful!

87
00:04:59,925 --> 00:05:03,136
Oh, it makes me want to rush
over to Ikebukuro this second!

88
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,680
Hey! What's Mr. Yuhei up to?

89
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,890
He knows Ikebukuro,

90
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:08,642
so let's have him
show us around.

91
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:11,603
We'll go check out this rematch
of the legend of Sleepy Hollow

92
00:05:11,603 --> 00:05:14,439
and then party
under the cherry blossoms!

93
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:16,983
‐ Mr. Sandshelt,
you're blocking the screen.

94
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,235
Please move.

95
00:05:18,235 --> 00:05:20,612
‐ Oh. Uh, my bad.

96
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:22,989
Hey, hold on!
Where do you get off treating me

97
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:24,574
like I'm some
flame in the ass?

98
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:26,576
Is it 'cause
you can't work for a foreigner?

99
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:28,119
Come on, now.

100
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:30,372
Aren't the Japanese supposed to
be kind and respectful

101
00:05:30,372 --> 00:05:32,958
towards their superiors?
Damn it!

102
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:35,961
My only allies are those who
raise themselves to an art form.

103
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:41,883
Every one of my adorable idols!

104
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,010
Only my angels
who spread happiness

105
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,846
over the world understand me,

106
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:48,306
and they always will, forever.

107
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:49,724
‐ Try to concentrate
on your job as president, sir.

108
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:51,268
‐ Hmm?

109
00:05:51,268 --> 00:05:54,145
‐ We already went for a party in
the cherry blossoms last week,

110
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:56,147
and Yuhei Hanejima isn't
available now

111
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:57,691
because he's back at his home.

112
00:05:57,691 --> 00:05:59,985
And, uh, why is it that
an American like yourself

113
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:01,987
has no grasp
of the English language?

114
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:04,656
‐ Ah!

115
00:06:04,656 --> 00:06:06,324
I swear.
What a dull bunch you are.

116
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:10,245
What I want is something new
with impact

117
00:06:10,245 --> 00:06:11,913
to get us out of
this rut we're in.

118
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:14,916
That's why I want to see
that mysterious headless rider.

119
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:19,129
Hold on.
I've got an idea!

120
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:22,841
Hiya. This is Sandshelt
of Jack O'Lantern calling.

121
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,801
Uh, it's Max.

122
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:30,932
<i>[piano music]</i>

123
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:33,894
‐ Half a year later.

124
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:37,564
The city hasn't changed at all.

125
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,065
He hasn't.

126
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:40,483
Or them.

127
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:42,694
Or them.
Or her.

128
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:46,531
Or them.
Or him.

129
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:47,782
And...

130
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:50,368
neither have we.

131
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,621
Sorry to take up your time,
Anri.

132
00:06:52,621 --> 00:06:55,373
I realize
it's kind of a weird request.

133
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:56,708
‐ It's all right, Mikado.

134
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,960
I don't mind,
though I'm afraid

135
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,837
I haven't been very helpful
so far.

136
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:03,214
‐ I was a little surprised
a first‐year student

137
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:05,550
would ask me
to show them around Ikebukuro.

138
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,469
‐ Even though we commute here
every day,

139
00:07:07,469 --> 00:07:09,763
we're surprisingly unfamiliar
with this area.

140
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:11,473
Like what kind of shops are
around,

141
00:07:11,473 --> 00:07:15,644
or where someone can go
to find a good place to eat.

142
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:17,312
‐ We only know Russia's sushi.

143
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:20,607
‐ Yeah, I know.

144
00:07:20,607 --> 00:07:23,818
‐ if only Masaomi were here.

145
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:27,072
‐ I wonder how he's doing.

146
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:28,365
‐ He's doing fine.

147
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:29,616
I'm sure of it.

148
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:30,909
‐ I hope so.

149
00:07:30,909 --> 00:07:34,079
‐ He is.

150
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,205
Hey, Namie.

151
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:36,706
‐ What?

152
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:38,875
‐ Want to go get something
to eat?

153
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:40,669
‐ Huh?

154
00:07:40,669 --> 00:07:42,754
‐ It's so boring around here.

155
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:45,590
I want to do something,
get out, and see some things.

156
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,008
Take in some culture.

157
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:48,760
It's pretty obvious
all kinds of things

158
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,595
are about to go down out there,

159
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:53,431
but it doesn't seem to have
much to do with me.

160
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:54,849
‐ If you and I went out to eat,

161
00:07:54,849 --> 00:07:57,102
what would we even talk about?

162
00:07:57,102 --> 00:08:00,980
‐ Things like the latest news
on your kid brother.

163
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:04,109
‐ Why?
Did something happen to Seiji?

164
00:08:04,109 --> 00:08:05,443
IZAYA: Not really.

165
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:07,362
He's been with Mika Harima,
as usual.

166
00:08:07,362 --> 00:08:10,156
It looks like
they're even deeper in love.

167
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,449
‐ I see.

168
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:12,617
As far as I'm concerned,

169
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:13,910
that's worthless information.

170
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:15,578
‐ [yawning]
It's the truth, though.

171
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:18,957
Maybe some news will come on
that will entertain me for once.

172
00:08:18,957 --> 00:08:21,584
<i>[exciting music]</i>

173
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:22,961
‐ News 666.

174
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:24,796
In our top story this evening...

175
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:26,464
‐ We'll be covering
the serial murders

176
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:28,758
that have rocked
Ikebukuro recently.

177
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,802
The perpetrator has
yet to be caught.

178
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:33,304
‐ The incident occurred
this morning before dawn.

179
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,473
Employees rushed
into a second‐floor room

180
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,766
after hearing a scream

181
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:38,768
and witnessed a gruesome scene.

182
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:40,645
What they saw
was an unconscious woman,

183
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:43,273
drenched head to toe in blood,
and a dead man,

184
00:08:43,273 --> 00:08:45,734
whose body was battered
beyond recognition,

185
00:08:45,734 --> 00:08:47,318
lying in front of her.

186
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:50,071
This is the third murder
to take place in this manner.

187
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:51,823
But there's been no evidence
as of yet

188
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:54,534
to point to a plausible suspect.

189
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:56,661
Someone in a wolf mask
was spotted

190
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:58,163
at the first crime scene.

191
00:08:58,163 --> 00:09:00,290
At the second,
witnesses reported seeing

192
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,667
a merman‐like figure
fleeing the site.

193
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,336
And today,
they were in a dinosaur mask

194
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,672
for this bizarre crime.

195
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:10,967
‐ I heard this scream,
so I ran out into the hall

196
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:13,136
to see what was going on.

197
00:09:13,136 --> 00:09:15,096
And‐‐and the door was open,

198
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:17,182
so I could see inside,

199
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:21,853
but when I looked in, um,
this dinosaur thing‐‐

200
00:09:21,853 --> 00:09:24,230
well, he looked like a monster,
you know?

201
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:27,108
Going at that guy's chest
with his bare hands.

202
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:29,194
[both groaning]
I could see him gouging‐‐

203
00:09:29,194 --> 00:09:31,279
‐ The titles due for release
this month are awesome.

204
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:32,363
‐ Huh?

205
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:33,907
‐ The irregular
magic high school.

206
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:37,702
‐ So no new volume
of a certain magical index?

207
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,788
‐ Dotachin,
you're into light novels?

208
00:09:39,788 --> 00:09:42,457
‐ Nope, those things are totally
beyond my understanding.

209
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:44,417
But that one's a pretty
interesting read.

210
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:47,545
‐ Sorry, man. Afraid there isn't
a new release out this month.

211
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:49,255
‐ If they stick
to their usual schedule,

212
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,132
it should come out
in a couple of months.

213
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:52,383
‐ Gotcha.

214
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:54,677
Give me a heads‐up
when it does, okay?

215
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:57,055
‐ Hollywood's at it again?
‐ Huh?

216
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:58,389
Who's Hollywood?

217
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:00,433
‐ It's that murderer's nickname.

218
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,018
It's all over the Internet, man.

219
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:04,437
That's what everyone started
calling him online.

220
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:06,231
‐ Why do they call him
"Hollywood"?

221
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:07,482
‐ Probably because he uses all

222
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:09,192
those badass costumes
and makeup.

223
00:10:09,192 --> 00:10:11,069
‐ It's so Hollywood!
Like that, huh?

224
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:13,905
‐ Mm‐hmm.
‐ I don't know his deal.

225
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:16,741
The way he kills isn't normal.
‐ It's beyond normal.

226
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,577
I hear it's actually way more
brutal than the reports say.

227
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:22,288
Apparently, all the media
were told to tone stuff down.

228
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,749
‐ Breaks down walls and doors
with his bare hands,

229
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:25,917
and then they say he strips

230
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,585
every shred of flesh
off his victims

231
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:29,587
so there's nothing left
but the bone.

232
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:31,840
‐ He takes people out
like he's some animal,

233
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,925
but he's human on the outside.

234
00:10:33,925 --> 00:10:35,343
The guy kind of sounds like

235
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:37,137
he's Death Gun from "SAO"
or something.

236
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:38,596
‐ I'm thinking
he's actually more like

237
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,098
Gastrea from "Black Bullet."

238
00:10:40,098 --> 00:10:41,641
‐ I'm thinking he's actually
more like

239
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:44,018
Yuuki Katakura from
"Double Brid."

240
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:45,520
‐ And I'm thinking to myself,

241
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,439
"Why are you guys enjoying this
so much?"

242
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:50,525
‐ Well, it's time for us to be
heading out.

243
00:10:50,525 --> 00:10:52,152
‐ We'll be seeing you two later.

244
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:53,695
‐ Where are you guys off to?

245
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:55,697
‐ We're heading out to see
Mikabu.

246
00:10:55,697 --> 00:10:57,240
‐ Said he wants to ask us
something,

247
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,867
but it's very hush‐hush.

248
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:02,162
‐ We'd like to take this time
to ask for your help.

249
00:11:02,162 --> 00:11:05,248
<i>[exciting music]</i>

250
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:10,295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

251
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:12,046
We'll be calling on you,
our viewers,

252
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,673
for any information you might
have.

253
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:17,594
‐ You've gotten to be
quite the celebrity, Celty.

254
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:19,304
‐ Guess I'll just go on TV,
then.

255
00:11:19,304 --> 00:11:20,471
‐ What? Seriously?

256
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:23,683
MAN:
Well, as a matter of fact...

257
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:24,893
‐ I'm kidding.

258
00:11:24,893 --> 00:11:26,477
I'm gonna go do that job now.

259
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:27,645
‐ Okay.

260
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:29,314
If anything happens,
get out quick.

261
00:11:29,314 --> 00:11:31,566
CELTY: Don't worry.
I'll be right back.

262
00:11:31,566 --> 00:11:33,151
‐ Celty!

263
00:11:33,151 --> 00:11:35,653
I'd be devastated
if something happened!

264
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:36,988
Please! No!

265
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:38,489
I don't know what I'd do
without you.

266
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:40,909
‐ Enough. I get it, all right?

267
00:11:44,329 --> 00:11:45,580
SHINRA: Celty?

268
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:46,873
Rub rub.
Rub rub.

269
00:11:46,873 --> 00:11:47,957
Ah!

270
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,340
‐ And now something special.

271
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:57,258
‐ An interview with someone

272
00:11:57,258 --> 00:11:59,886
who's a big hit
with women these days.

273
00:11:59,886 --> 00:12:02,180
MAN: Yuhei Hanajima.
Date of birth unknown.

274
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:04,849
Estimated age‐‐
21.

275
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:08,603
He debuted in
"Vampire Ninja: Carmilla Saizo."

276
00:12:08,603 --> 00:12:10,438
His good looks
and knockout performance

277
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,023
ignited his popularity.

278
00:12:12,023 --> 00:12:14,734
Appearing nonstop
in high‐profile TV shows

279
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,319
and films,
his versatility gained him

280
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:19,113
critical acclaim, even overseas.

281
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,032
‐ [vocalizing]

282
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:22,700
MAN: Not content being
just an actor,

283
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,745
he also crossed into
variety shows.

284
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:27,413
On the show "How Much Can You
Increase

285
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,249
the Worth of a Million
Yen in a Month,"

286
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:33,836
he used his wits to increase
his capital to 1.2 billion yen.

287
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:36,381
On a hidden camera show,
he was surrounded by Yakuza

288
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:38,216
and pressured to cut off
his pinky.

289
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:40,385
As he was about to chop it off,

290
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:44,138
the crew rushed in
and stopped him just in time.

291
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:46,432
‐ When it comes
to whatever Yuhei's thinking,

292
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:47,934
I honestly draw a total blank,

293
00:12:47,934 --> 00:12:50,728
since the guy's usually
as silent as a Buddha.

294
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:53,731
Even to me, he's all
"no, thanks" when we talk.

295
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:56,192
Like this poster?
It was my idea,

296
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:58,945
but I heard some talk that
Yuhei didn't really like it.

297
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:02,323
No reaction whatsoever.
Like a cold fish.

298
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:04,325
I got fed up, went to America,

299
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:06,494
and he was all "no problem"
and stuff.

300
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:08,955
I swear, what a prima donna.
Aren't I?

301
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:11,541
MAN: And we've managed to get
an exclusive interview

302
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:12,750
with this man.

303
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:15,753
We'll see
the real Yuhei Hanejima.

304
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:17,171
WOMAN: In your personal life,

305
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,798
you're known
for being somewhat poker‐faced.

306
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,300
How did this come about?

307
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,927
‐ It's because my older brother
had violent mood swings,

308
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:24,971
so I tried not to be like him
while growing up.

309
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:27,849
Still, I do have a lot
of respect for him despite that.

310
00:13:27,849 --> 00:13:29,100
‐ Hmph.

311
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:31,185
WOMAN: I see. All right.
‐ Shizuo.

312
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:32,520
‐ Huh?
‐ Let's get going.

313
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,688
‐ Right.

314
00:13:33,688 --> 00:13:36,107
‐ "Carmilla Saizou:
The Beginning."

315
00:13:36,107 --> 00:13:38,901
‐ Carmilla Saizou is definitely
a force to be reckoned with.

316
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:51,289
EMILIA: All right.
That should do it.

317
00:13:51,289 --> 00:13:56,044
I'm completely finished.

318
00:13:56,044 --> 00:13:57,503
I want to thank you
for allowing us

319
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:01,507
to perform
this illicit research.

320
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,135
‐ Emilia,
it's not illicit research.

321
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:06,471
It's scientific research.

322
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:07,430
‐ Oh, my!

323
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:08,848
I'm sorry about that,

324
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:09,807
but I sincerely wish

325
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:11,142
you would call me Mother.

326
00:14:11,142 --> 00:14:12,977
If you did,
I would most certainly rain down

327
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:15,646
a torrent of appreciation
in return for that.

328
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:18,441
Or maybe Mommy.
Mamma Mia.

329
00:14:22,195 --> 00:14:23,488
‐ What's wrong?

330
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:25,740
‐ Nothing.
It's just that, normally,

331
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:27,450
you'd be jabbing me in the ribs
by now

332
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:31,662
or yanking my cheek out
like this.

333
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:35,833
‐ Actually, I am seducing you.

334
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,919
‐ [sighs]
[doorbell rings]

335
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,087
What the?

336
00:14:39,087 --> 00:14:41,839
Aw, just when
it was getting good.

337
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:45,051
Coming.

338
00:14:45,051 --> 00:14:47,428
‐ Hi!
A full‐grown Japanese male.

339
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:50,640
It's really you, isn't it,
Dr. Shinra Kishitani?

340
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:52,433
‐ Huh? Hey!
Hold on!

341
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:54,936
EMILIA: [laughing and squealing]

342
00:14:54,936 --> 00:14:57,522
SHINRA: [muffled groaning]

343
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,567
‐ Ah! Look at you!
Celty!

344
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,194
‐ Hey! Wait!

345
00:15:03,194 --> 00:15:06,197
EMILIA: I've been waiting
for this moment for so long!

346
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:09,117
‐ Who are you?

347
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:10,326
‐ Oh.

348
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:11,536
How rude of me.

349
00:15:11,536 --> 00:15:13,287
My name is Emilia, of course.

350
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:16,165
I happen to be your father,
Shingen's, second wife.

351
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:19,210
So exciting.
We got married in America.

352
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:20,378
BOTH: What?

353
00:15:20,378 --> 00:15:22,880
SHINGEN: Call her "Mother."

354
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,633
‐ What? Dad?
When'd you get here?

355
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,887
‐ Well, the thing is...

356
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:34,475
While I can't deny I've been
thinking about my future

357
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:38,104
where Shinra's concerned...

358
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:40,773
it's nothing concrete
like marriage yet.

359
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:43,317
‐ You're basically living
like a common law couple.

360
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:45,862
‐ Ah!
Don't sneak up like that!

361
00:15:45,862 --> 00:15:49,615
SHINGEN: Well, you did agree to
be an experimental subject

362
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:51,909
on the condition that
a female researcher

363
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:53,703
would be the point of contact.

364
00:15:53,703 --> 00:15:55,204
That's why I'm using this‐‐

365
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:56,581
‐ That's not the problem!

366
00:15:56,581 --> 00:15:58,833
SHINGEN: You've already
married into my family,

367
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,126
more or less, Celty.

368
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:02,253
I want you to treat Emilia
like a mother.

369
00:16:02,253 --> 00:16:03,546
‐ Mm‐hmm, mm‐hmm!

370
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:06,465
‐ Thanks a lot.

371
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:09,218
‐ I must admit that never in my
wildest dreams

372
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:13,181
did I think I'd be accepting
a Dullahan as Shinra's bride.

373
00:16:13,181 --> 00:16:15,933
A headless rider.
A headless bride.

374
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:18,269
A headless klutz.

375
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:22,064
Interacting with you is like
one eye‐opener after another.

376
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:24,567
‐ Don't you have any second
thoughts about taking advantage

377
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,195
of your son's bride for
your research?

378
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:30,531
‐ It truly pains me to do so,
but it can't be helped.

379
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:32,950
I'm afraid I can't afford to
turn down a request

380
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:35,286
that's straight
from Nebula headquarters.

381
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:39,457
‐ So we'll be cutting away
at you a lot.

382
00:16:39,457 --> 00:16:42,043
‐ Whatever.

383
00:16:42,043 --> 00:16:44,378
Could you just pay me
for this job?

384
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:47,256
SHINGEN: Emilia,
please give her the money.

385
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:48,799
‐ You only need to give
the word,

386
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:50,468
and it shall be done, dear.

387
00:16:50,468 --> 00:16:52,553
Payment as promised.

388
00:16:56,057 --> 00:17:01,520
[cash register clinks]

389
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,648
‐ Received. Thank you.

390
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:05,650
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

391
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:08,986
Wow, it's hard to believe
I made a million yen

392
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:11,364
in just one week.
[gasps]

393
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:13,908
I'm gonna use this
to buy Shinra some new glasses.

394
00:17:13,908 --> 00:17:15,701
And then‐‐
I know.

395
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:18,913
Why don't I treat him
to something really good to eat?

396
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:20,456
[laughs]

397
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:22,458
He's always said he wanted
to eat pickled yellowtail,

398
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:23,834
hasn't he?

399
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:25,711
Wait. Is yellowtail
even in season now?

400
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:28,673
‐ Excuse me.

401
00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:31,342
I'm sorry to bother you,
but do you have a minute?

402
00:17:31,342 --> 00:17:33,177
I'm Fukumi with Dio TV,

403
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:35,012
and I'd like to ask you
a question or two,

404
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,180
if you wouldn't mind.

405
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:39,016
‐ Crap. Don't tell me.

406
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:41,018
‐ I'm currently reporting
on traffic etiquette

407
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:42,395
here in the city.

408
00:17:42,395 --> 00:17:44,689
And your motorcyle‐‐
it doesn't seem to have

409
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:46,399
lights or a license plate.

410
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:49,235
Were you aware those are
violations of the law?

411
00:17:49,235 --> 00:17:51,988
Would it be safe to assume
that you are the black rider?

412
00:17:51,988 --> 00:17:53,322
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

413
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:54,865
Uh?

414
00:17:54,865 --> 00:17:56,909
I'd appreciate a comment.

415
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:58,411
How do you justify this?

416
00:17:58,411 --> 00:17:59,870
Riding around
on a dangerous bike?

417
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:01,330
‐ What should I do?

418
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:03,583
I can't say, "I'm a monster,
so please overlook it."

419
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:05,835
Huh? Maybe I could.

420
00:18:05,835 --> 00:18:07,878
If I show him something
unbelievable,

421
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:09,213
it might get edited out,

422
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:11,424
and it might look like CG
if it's aired.

423
00:18:11,424 --> 00:18:14,093
‐ Hmm?
What's this?

424
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:18,139
"This is a horse, so it has
no headlights or license plate."

425
00:18:18,139 --> 00:18:20,808
Come on.
Are you joking?

426
00:18:28,566 --> 00:18:30,067
‐ Is everything clear now?

427
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,444
If so, I'll be on my way.

428
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:33,571
‐ [whimpering]

429
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:39,118
KINNOSUKE: Hey.

430
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:41,162
Where do you think you're going?

431
00:18:41,162 --> 00:18:43,497
Riding without lights
is a punishable offense,

432
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:45,833
even on motorless modes
of transportation.

433
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,877
Monster.

434
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:50,087
‐ Uh?

435
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:52,632
[neighing]

436
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:55,801
‐ Call the studio!

437
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:59,096
[police siren wailing]

438
00:19:01,724 --> 00:19:06,854
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

439
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:12,985
<i>♪ ♪</i>

440
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,278
‐ Not good.

441
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:16,447
Not good. Not good.
Not good. Not good!

442
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:36,092
‐ It's a huge black object!

443
00:19:42,348 --> 00:19:44,975
[cell phone ringing]

444
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:47,436
‐ Oh, you finally picked up.

445
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:49,146
So, Celty, looks like

446
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,399
you've got yourself into
some trouble there.

447
00:19:51,399 --> 00:19:53,109
But that was
a pretty slick trick.

448
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,152
Using your shadows to make
copies of yourself,

449
00:19:55,152 --> 00:19:56,737
your bike, and that glider,

450
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:59,323
and then launching them off
the roof to use as a decoy.

451
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:01,951
Anyway, I think starting today,

452
00:20:01,951 --> 00:20:03,786
things are gonna get pretty busy
for a while,

453
00:20:03,786 --> 00:20:06,455
so there's something
we need to be clear about.

454
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:11,001
Until the chaos settles down,
stay away from my workplace.

455
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:13,838
I'll email you the details, but
I called so that you don't

456
00:20:13,838 --> 00:20:16,549
come by before you
get a chance to read it.

457
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:18,342
Later!
Best of luck.

458
00:20:18,342 --> 00:20:22,388
MAN: The mysterious object is
circling above Ikebukuro
Station.

459
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:24,098
Its destination‐‐

460
00:20:24,098 --> 00:20:26,809
‐ What's with him?

461
00:20:31,605 --> 00:20:34,608
No, it's gone!
It's gone!

462
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:36,026
I dropped it somewhere!

463
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:38,654
I must've dropped it!

464
00:20:45,286 --> 00:20:47,371
[engines approaching]

465
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:52,126
‐ Hey! It's the Black Rider!

466
00:20:52,126 --> 00:20:55,129
‐ Huh?
‐ Let's get our 10 million yen!

467
00:20:55,129 --> 00:20:57,590
MAN: Whoo‐hoo!

468
00:20:57,590 --> 00:21:00,176
[men shouting excitedly]

469
00:21:04,388 --> 00:21:06,140
‐ Did you see that reward
on the net?

470
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:08,100
‐ Yeah! A cool 10 mil!

471
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,560
‐ Think it's Celty?

472
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:11,645
‐ Let's go see.

473
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:19,737
MAN: You little brats
disrespecting the Dollars?

474
00:21:19,737 --> 00:21:22,698
‐ No, we're not.

475
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:24,074
‐ You bastards.

476
00:21:24,074 --> 00:21:27,787
You're a bunch
of damn petty thieves!

477
00:21:29,038 --> 00:21:32,082
[both panting]

478
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:38,422
‐ Like I said, you're so lucky.

479
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:39,757
Don't just stand there.
Come on.

480
00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:41,258
You want to see an urban legend?

481
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:45,763
MIKADO: It's true.
We haven't changed.

482
00:21:45,763 --> 00:21:48,432
‐ The black bike!
The headless rider!

483
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:51,602
<i>♪ ♪</i>

484
00:21:51,602 --> 00:21:52,937
MIKADO: Compared to back then,

485
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:55,523
a lot of things have changed.

486
00:21:55,523 --> 00:21:58,567
<i>[dreamy music]</i>

487
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:01,862
<i>♪ ♪</i>

488
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:04,240
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

489
00:22:05,241 --> 00:22:07,284
[riders cheering]

490
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:13,123
[all laughing]

491
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:15,835
MIKADO: But nothing about us
has changed.

492
00:22:18,629 --> 00:22:20,422
‐ Huh? Not watching?

493
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:21,841
‐ Nah.

494
00:22:21,841 --> 00:22:24,468
[yawns]

495
00:22:24,468 --> 00:22:26,637
MIKADO: Or should have.

496
00:22:28,639 --> 00:22:31,767
<i>[man singing in Japanese]</i>

497
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:38,774
<i>♪ ♪</i>

498
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:59,521
MAN: Ikebukuro.
The city that never sleeps.

499
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:02,900
Night and day, people come and
go, meeting and parting.

500
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:05,611
Suspicious murderer.
Suspicious new students.

501
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:07,196
Suspicious Russians.

502
00:24:07,196 --> 00:24:10,407
Next time, "Harmony Is
the Greatest of Virtues."

